iv class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">3.<\/span><span> Label sorting tubes for samples<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">     a. Sample<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">     b. Aqua live\/Dead Only<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">4.<\/span><span> Label TWO sets of collection tubes for each cell type and put <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">  1XPBS in each tube<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">     a. Alpha<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">     b. Beta<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">     c. Acinar<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">5.<\/span><span> Prepare 2% FBS (50ml 1XPBS + 1ml FBS), keep on ice<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">     Note:<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;\">     Keep 2% FBS, 1XPBS, trypsin and FBS on ice<\/span><\/div><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"07109850DAA111EBAA342BF0A0EB0EFC","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":6,"unit":"mL","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"64F575D0DAA111EBAA342BF0A0EB0EFC","order_id":3,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":500,"unit":"\u00b5l","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1206337,"guid":"97497430DAA311EBAA342BF0A0EB0EFC","previous_id":1206310,"previous_guid":"DBD6EBD0DAA011EBAA342BF0A0EB0EFC","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"231CE05B3DCA4C309184CCBCBDC5F7E6","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"PROCEDURE"}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"A43EFAC24E7C4EFA9DC6199E8EB10FD2","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">1.<\/span><span> Incubate islets.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">2.<\/span><span> Combine all islets into TWO <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> conical tubes.<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">3.<\/span><span> Centrifuge 4min, 1200rpm, RT.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">4.<\/span><span> Take off supernatant and use supernatant to rinse residual islets out of flask. Spin again, 4min, 1200rpm, RT.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">5.<\/span><span> Add <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span> 0.05% trypsin to each 50ml tube, pipette up and down (<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">NOTE:<\/span><span> re-suspend in 1ml trypsin using P1000 and then add additional <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> ).<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">6.<\/span><span> Incubate at <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> (water bath) for 9min. Pipette up and down every 3min. (t = 7min, 4min, 1min, 0min).<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">7.<\/span><span> Remove tubes from water bath and add 1ml 100% FBS into tube to inhibit trypsin activity.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">8.<\/span><span> To remove undispersed material, passage contents of two <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> conical tubes through ONE strainer into ONE <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span> conical in the following order.\u00a0 (<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">NOTE:<\/span><span> use p1000, tip is on strainer, pressure, swirl. tips).<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> a. Add <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> 100% FBS to the empty <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> conical tube 1 and passage contents of tube 1 through the strainer.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> b. Add <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> 100% FBS to the second empty <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> conical tube and passage contents of tubes through the strainer.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> c. Swirl tube, and if clumps visible vortex quickly (2 sec).<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">9. <\/span><span>Going forward, cells remain in ONE conical tube. Spins occur at RT.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">10.<\/span><span> Centrifuge: 4min, 1200rpm. Take off supernatant. Re-suspend in 25ml 1XPBS. Vortex quickly, then centrifuge 4min, 1200rpm. Take off supernatant.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">11.<\/span><span> Re-suspend in 1-2ml 2% FBS.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">12.<\/span><span> Count cells (<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> cells, <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> trypan blue, <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> into either side of a Countess chamber.\u00a0 Or make dilution as needed).<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">13.<\/span><span> Adjust volume so cells are at a concentration of 5x106 cells\/ml in 2% FBS.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">14.<\/span><span> For Aqua Live\/Dead Only negative control: Remove 100,000 cells (<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> ) and put in FACS tube labeled Aqua. Add <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> 2%FBS for final volume of <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> . Store on ice until step 20.<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">15.<\/span><span> Add ALL FOUR primary antibodies to cells (see below for detailed information; different batches of antibody may require optimization)-<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>       a. <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">HICO-4F9<\/span><span>(HPi1): 1:100<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>       b. <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">HIC3-2D12<\/span><span>(HPa3): 1:50<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>       c. <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">HIC1-1C10<\/span><span>(HPx2): 1:500<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>       d. <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">NPTDase:<\/span><span>1:270 (TBD by each lot)<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">16.<\/span><span> Incubate for 30 min on ice. Swirl tube every 10 min.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">17.<\/span><span> Centrifuge: 4 min, 1200rpm. Remove supernatant.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">18.<\/span><span> Wash by re-suspending in <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> PBS, centrifuge 4 min, 1200rpm. Re-suspend in 2% FBS to bring concentration back to 5x106 cells\/ml.<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">19.<\/span><span> Prepare Aqua reagents: Add <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Component B to 1 vial of Component A.\u00a0 Combined Aqua reagents (good for 2 weeks after constitution); <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">LIVE\/DEAD\u2122 Fixable Aqua Dead Cell Stain Kit<\/span><span>, for 405 nm excitation, <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.thermofisher.com\/order\/catalog\/product\/L34957#\/L34957\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">Invitrogen: L34957<\/span><\/a><\/div><br\/><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">20. <\/span><span>Add ALL THREE secondary antibodies at 1:200 and Aqua reagents. See below for secondary antibodies information.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">21.<\/span><span> Use <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> aqua reagents to each <\/div><div class = \"text-block\">of cells.\u00a0<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">      a. Add <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> aqua reagents to the Aqua Live\/Dead Only tube.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">      b. Add appropriate amount (\u00b5l) of aqua reagents to the sample.<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">22.<\/span><span> Incubate for 30 min at <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> , with tubes wrapped in foil. Mix (swirl) every 10 minutes.<\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">23.<\/span><span> Centrifuge:\u00a0 4 min, 1200 rpm.\u00a0 Take off supernatant.\u00a0 Wash:\u00a0 re-suspend in <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span> PBS, centrifuge 4 min, 1200rpm. Re-suspend in 2% FBS buffer to <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">5x10<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;vertical-align:super;\">6<\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">cells\/ml<\/span><span>. Filter through strainer (attached to the blue tube) to transfer to FACS tube.<\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">24. <\/span><span>Centrifuge Aqua Live\/Dead Only cells 2 minutes at 2K g, was in <\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">1XPBS, spin again, resuspend in <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> 1X PBS. Wash Aqua-only with <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> . Resuspend in <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> 2% FBS.<\/div><br\/><div style = \"text-align :; float : ;\"><img style = \"\" src = \"https:\/\/s3.amazonaws.com\/protocols-files\/files\/d69z4kcn.jpg\" \/><\/div><br\/><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"C24C3230DAA311EBAA342BF0A0EB0EFC","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":50,"unit":"mL","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"F5AAFBC0DAA311EBAA342BF0A0EB0EFC","order_id":3,"type_id":3,"title":"amount